pull.title: Rename member field according to the style guide
pull.body:
After #10193, approx. five instances of this warning are printed when compiling with `-Wshadow`:

```
In file included from txmempool.cpp:14:
./reverse_iterator.h:20:22: warning: declaration shadows a field of 'reverse_range<T>' [-Wshadow]
    reverse_range(T &x) : x(x) {}
                     ^
./reverse_iterator.h:17:8: note: previous declaration is here
    T &x;
       ^
1 warning generated.
```

events.body: If you're going to change this anyway, would you mind switching to the style guidelines? (m_x for the field, x for the parameter).

events.message: Rename member field according to the style guide.

events.body:
@sipa Like this?

Any other issue with the file?

rename.from: Do not shadow a field of 'reverse_range<T>'
rename.to: Rename member field according to the style guide

events.body: utACK 4d4fb33fce0803f9c923307bdf. This gives the same binaries and does not conflict with any open pull request tagged for 0.15, so should be fine to merge.
